<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-122-049 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 882 616</DOCID><JOURNAL>UNIX World  July 1991 v8 n7 p51(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sippl the survivor. (Roger Sippl, chairman of Informix Software,Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poole, Gary Andrew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Roger Sippl, chairman of Informix Software Inc, is a Hodgkin'sdisease survivor, and he credits his remarkable recovery withgiving him a unique ability to deal philosophically with the upsand downs of the computer business.andP;  He also believes that goingthrough the ordeal of cancer and recovery has given him thediscipline to reach his goals.andP;  His beliefs are being tested as hedeals with a $46 million loss by Informix in 1990.andP;  The cancer,which was diagnosed almost immediately after he arrived atcollege, also influenced his choice of career.andP;  Sippl wasoriginally planning on becoming a doctor but his need for a jobpushed him into computer science.andP;  After graduation he beganworking on database management systems.andP;  He soon wanted to createa company where he could develop a database system that wouldconsist of a relational database, a report writer and a screenbuilding package.andP;  After a long struggle he succeeded in raising$184,000 to start his company, Informix, which shipped its firstproduct in 1981.andP;  By 1985 Informix had revenues of over $10million, and went public in 1986.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Informix Software Inc. (Officials and employees).andO;Topic:     BiographyChief Executive OfficersManagement Style.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Roger Sippl. (portrait)Person:    Sippl, Roger (Biography).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>